## Executive Overview

STARFRAME SF-1 LATTICE represents the evolutionary expansion of STARFRAME SF-1 from a structural intelligence framework into a fully distributed lattice architecture.

While STARFRAME SF-1 established the concept of adaptive structural intelligence, STARFRAME SF-1 LATTICE introduces the next stage:

> Intelligence is no longer embedded within the structure.

> Intelligence emerges from the structure.

The system transforms the airframe from a collection of engineered components into a continuously interacting lattice network capable of:

* Load distribution
* Structural adaptation
* Aerodynamic interaction
* Thermal balancing
* Telecommunications routing
* Autonomous stabilization

The architecture becomes the direct predecessor to:

* Boeing 220-G Lattice Core System
* Boeing 220-G Global
* Future PI220 Aerospace Platforms

